<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-UvsvVAsvaHyQUSn9FipNfg" name="new_toolmentor,_ZMAicHj7EdyhRNciHt44hg" guid="-UvsvVAsvaHyQUSn9FipNfg" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Before creating a configuration record, determine which configuration platform details have a testing impact. You must&#xD;
    create a configuration record for each testing platform on which a test is run.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Before creating a configuration record, you must create configuration attribute and configuration value records.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    For more information, see the CQTM online Help topics &lt;em>Creating a configuration attribute record&lt;/em> and&#xD;
    &lt;em>Creating a configuration value record&lt;/em>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Tool Steps&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;div>&#xD;
    &lt;div class=&quot;skipspace&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;div class=&quot;skipspace&quot;>&#xD;
            To create a configuration record:&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
        &lt;ol>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;span>Log in to a database that supports IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearQuest&amp;reg; Test Manager.&lt;/span>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;span>Using a supported Rational ClearQuest client:&lt;/span> &#xD;
                &lt;ol type=&quot;a&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        &lt;span>From a &lt;span class=&quot;keyword&quot;>Rational ClearQuest for Windows client&lt;/span>, click &lt;span                         class=&quot;menucascade&quot;>&lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Actions&lt;/span> &amp;gt; &lt;span                         class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>New&lt;/span>&lt;/span> and from the Choose Record Type window, click &lt;span                         class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>TMConfiguration&lt;/span> and then click &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>OK&lt;/span>.&lt;/span>&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        &lt;span>From a &lt;span class=&quot;keyword&quot;>Rational ClearQuest Web client&lt;/span>, click &lt;span                         class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>New&lt;/span> and then select &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>TMConfiguration&lt;/span> and&#xD;
                        click &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Go&lt;/span>.&lt;/span>&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ol>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;span>From the &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Configuration&lt;/span> page:&lt;/span> &#xD;
                &lt;ol type=&quot;a&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        &lt;span>Type a configuration name in the &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Name&lt;/span> field.&lt;/span>&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        &lt;span>Type an optional description in the &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Description&lt;/span> field.&lt;/span>&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        &lt;span>Add a value to the &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Configuration Attribute List&lt;/span> by clicking&#xD;
                        &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Add&lt;/span> and then selecting one or more configuration values from the&#xD;
                        Browse Record Type window.&lt;/span>&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ol>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;span>In the &lt;span class=&quot;keyword&quot;>Rational ClearQuest for Windows client&lt;/span>, click &lt;span                 class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>OK&lt;/span>. In the &lt;span class=&quot;keyword&quot;>Rational ClearQuest Web client&lt;/span>, click&#xD;
                &lt;span class=&quot;uicontrol&quot;>Save&lt;/span>.&lt;/span>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ol>&#xD;
        &lt;div class=&quot;skipspace&quot;>&#xD;
            After creating a configuration record, you can associate it with a configured test case or test suite record.&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;div class=&quot;skipspace&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            For more information, see the CQTM online Help topic&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>Creating a configuration record,&amp;nbsp;Using a&#xD;
            configuration record&lt;/em>, &lt;em>and Modifying a configuration record.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em>&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;/div>&#xD;
&lt;/div></mainDescription>
